                <h5><b></b>
                    RELOCATION OF YOUR PERSONAL HOUSEHOLD GOODS                   
                </h5> 
                Dear {!Salutation}, 
                <br/>
                <p style="text-align:justify">
                    Thank you for nominating Grace Relocations to handle the relocation of your personal &amp; household effects
                    from from {!qte.Enquiry_Id__r.Origin_City__c} to {!qte.Enquiry_Id__r.Destination_City__c} be assured of our best services not only at origin but also until delivery.             
                </p> 
                <p style="text-align:justify">
                    We would like to inform you that our as per the terms agreed with our commercial proposal, the scope of
                    the work covers the following:
                </p>
                <h4>
                    <u>Scope of Services: -</u>               
                </h4>
                <div style="text-align:justify">                   
                               
                    <ul type="square">
                        <li> Full Care &amp; Attention</li>
                        <li>                          
                            Use of best industry standard, mix of new &amp; re-cycled transit worthy packing material
                            that includes cardboard cartons, white paper, padding paper, cardboard rolls, tissue paper,
                            wooden casing as per requirements, masking tapes, Special marking for packages containing Fragile
                            &amp; Delicate items to ensure safe handling &amp; no damage. 
                            
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <ul type="square">
                        <li>
                            Trained &amp; Skilled Packers &amp; Loaders 
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <ul type="square">
                        <li>
                            Transportation will be arranged using suitable transit worthy vehicles available at the time. 
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>                
                <div style="text-align:justify">                   
                    <u><b>Scope of Work (Household Moving):</b></u> Packing of the effects at residence at origin inclusive
                    of industry standard materials, Team supervision, dismantling of normal furniture, complete marking 
                    on the packages with items name, detailed inventory; labour; Loading, Local or Long Distance
                    transportation in suitable transit worthy vehicles on Chartered or Groupage consignment basis,
                    with escort, single point unloading at the destination location/site; immediate / same day unpacking,
                    assembly of normal furniture, placement of items and removal of debris.
                </div>
                <br/>
                <div style="text-align:justify">                   
                    <u><b>Scope of Work (Car Moving):</b></u> Securing, Lashing, Loading, Unloading, and Delivery on door
                    to door basis.  All cars will be transported in car carrier trailers (subject to availability). 
                    The transit time will also depend on availability of trailer service. The car will be driven down 
                    to and collected from the point of operation of the trailer service.  The transferee will have to
                    ensure the automobile has fuel up to at least half the tank capacity at the time of pick up. The Car
                    registration book, tax book, Pollution Under Control certificate and valid comprehensive insurance
                    policy (originals) are required en route and must be handed over to our office prior to dispatch.
                    <b>In sectors where the car carrier service is not available, the movement will be in exclusive vehicles.
                        The tariff for transportation will be as mentioned in the tariff for movement of household goods.
                    </b>
                </div>
                <h4>
                    <u>Important:-</u>               
                </h4> 
                <div style="text-align:justify">                   
                    <b>Appliances:</b> Please be advised that - all your appliances - washer, dryer refrigerator, 
                    and inverters must be prepared for transportation by the manufacturers authorised dealer or your service agent.
                    For e.g. the acid slurry of the inverter must be drained out from the batteries, gas from cylinders must be
                    released, all moving parts must be secured / locked for transportation. All your computers and accessories 
                    should be disconnected prior to commencement of packing. Besides, locking/ unlocking or precautions, if any,
                    to be taken on these computers and accessories which require the manufacturerâ€™s or their authorised dealers
                    technical assistance to make such items suitable for safe transport, must be organised by your self at least
                    24 hours before start of packing.</div> 
                <br/>
                <div style="text-align:justify">                   
                   <b>Pots &amp; Plants:</b> While we will arrange for the relocation of the potted plants, 
                    which will be subject to availability of space in the truck, please note that carriage of potted plants
                    will be done solely at Owners Risk since no insurance is undertaken by the Underwriters for transit risks
                    against damages.</div>        
                <br/>
                <div style="text-align:justify">                   
                    <b>2 Wheelers:</b> The copies of 2 wheeler registration book, tax book, Pollution Under Control 
                    certificate (Original) and valid comprehensive insurance policy are required en-route and must be handed 
                    over to our office prior to despatch. A checklist will be made for external visuals and fitted accessories of
                    the 2 wheeler at the time of handover. The fuel tank of 2 wheeler must be empty at the time of handover at 
                    origin.</div>    
                <br/>
                <div style="text-align:justify">                   
                   <b>Cars:</b> The copies of Car registration book, tax book, Pollution Under Control certificate
                    (Original) and valid comprehensive insurance policy are required en-route and must be handed over to our 
                    office prior to dispatch. A checklist will be made for external visuals and fitted accessories of the car
                    at the time of handover. The car must have minimum 10 liters of fuel in the tank at the time of handover
                    at origin. The car will be driven from the pick-up point to the loading site at origin and from unloading
                    site to delivery point at destination</div>    
                <br/>
                <div style="text-align:justify">
                    The transit insurance of the car will only cover risk while the car is loaded on the trailer / container while 
                    in transit. It does not cover the accidental damages occurred while the car is driven from the pick-up 
                    point/residence at origin to the loading site via our warehouse and at destination from unloading site to 
                    the delivery address. The existing comprehensive insurance of the car itself will cover the risk during such 
                    movement.</div>
                <h4><b>
                    <u>Following services are not covered in the above scope of the services and shall be charged extra:</u> </b>                   
                </h4>
                <div style="text-align:justify">
                    <ul>
                        <li>Any professional third party handymen services such as electrician/carpenter /plumber for
                            removal/dismantling and fixing/assembly of Air conditioners, Geysers, Fans Light Fittings,
                            wall mounted TV, Ductable Coolers, Washing Machines, Water Filter/RO and any other 
                            special/designer furniture, hanging of pictures/paintings and artifacts on walls or
                            GAS / Material / Pipe charges as per actual &amp; No guaranty is given for Gas leakage,
                            Pipe breakage or bend, technical faults.  
                        </li>  
                        <li>Multiple pick-ups/deliveries, vehicles/labour detention and overtime beyond normal working hours,
                            working on Sundays and Public holidays.</li>   
                        <li>Staggered origin/destination services. </li>   
                        <li>Handling of items which cannot be accessed through a normal door/staircase/elevator.
                        </li>
                        <li>Society/landlord permission and fees, if applicable.</li>
                        <li>Charges towards shuttle service due to access/parking restrictions. </li>
                        <li>Delivery to high rise buildings and use of extra manpower for walking stairs beyond 2nd floor, hoist. </li>
                        <li>Handling of heavy objects like pianos, safes, etc.</li>
                        <li>Octroi, expediting charges and inter-state border expenses and taxes.</li>
                        <li>Mandatory labour union charges which are applicable in Pondicherry, Kerala, Coimbatore, some 
                            areas in Mumbai, Pune, Maharashtra, ranging between 5,500/- to 12,500/- per vehicle load and
                            will be billed at actuals.</li>
                        <li>Storage related costs on intra-India household goods shipments</li>                
                    </ul> 
                </div>
                <h4><b>
                    <u>Any force majeure situation. </u> </b>                   
                </h4>
                <div style="text-align:justify">
                    <ul>
                        <li>If no value is declared for individual item / individual box 10,000/-. Claim would be settled @ 1000/- Per item / per box. 
                        </li>  
                        <li>Multiple pick-ups/deliveries, vehicles/labour detention and overtime beyond normal working hours,
                            working on Sundays and Public holidays.</li>   
                        <li>Electrical Items like fridge, TV &amp; home appliances: No guaranty of technical &amp; internal
                            faults.</li>   
                        <li>Modular furniture  which have more than five parts will have to be dismantled &amp; 
                            assembled through manufacturer or authorized dealer by user / shipper.
                        </li>
                        <li>Any claim should be intimated and lodged within 72 hours of delivery of the goods. 
                            In case of Car/Bike, claim should be intimated and lodged within 12 hours In case of Car/Bike
                            or other articles only exterior damages will be entertained, no claim will be paid for any
                            internal or mechanical fault.</li>
                        <li>We do not accept to move perishable goods, Jewelry, Arms &amp; Ammunitions, Hazardous material
                            like Crackers, Explosives, Chemicals, Filled &amp; Empty Gas Cylinder, Battery Acids, and Inflammable
                            Oils; such as Diesel, Petrol, Kerosene, Gasoline, Narcotics &amp; Counter brand Items. </li>
                        <li>All items that require dismantling and assembling should be done before the packing date by client,
                            if these services are not taken from Grace Relocations Private Limited.</li>
                    </ul> 
                </div>
